            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3596889&cid=43317745">(#43317745)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43317745" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>More like 20mph top speed for these fixed multiotor systems.</p><p>The problem is the fixed design of the rotor, it has been designed to hover efficiently.<br>To fly fast you need adjustable rotors to compensate for the wind speed.<br>It affects your virtual angle of attack or air speed vs rotor speed.</p><p>Above 20mph this design becomes very inefficient at moving air.</p></div>
