        <article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43318043" data-cid="43318043">
    <div id="comment_43318043">
        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:50mph? in your dreams."><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:50mph? in your dreams.<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~140Mandak262Jamuna" class="author" title="author name and user ID">140Mandak262Jamuna (970587) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3596889&cid=43318043">(#43318043)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43318043" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body">Even the variable pitch rotors used in full sized helicopters are not all that efficient compared to fixed wing aircraft. (Here "efficiency" is defined by the energy used to move payload). You see the fixed wing aircraft produce enough thrust to overcome drag and the aerodynamics of pushing the wing into air creates lift. Anything that hovers must produce enough thrust to overcome the weight. Typically in a fixed wing aircraft the Lift (or weight) to drag ratio is above 10. Thus you are using much smaller engine for the same weight in fixed wing aircraft. So purely by fuel efficiency point of view, rotary wing aircraft can never compete with fixed wing aircraft.</div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_43318043">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3596889" data-cid="43318043">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="43318043" data-pid="43318043" data-cid="43318043"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default show-parent" href=""><i class="fa fa-level-up"></i> Parent</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default menu-trigger moderatebtn"><i class="fa fa-gavel"></i> Moderate
                    
                        <div class="menu menu-moderate">
                            <p class="info-message text-info"><span class="fa fa-info-circle"></span>
				
					You need to be logged in to be eligible to receive moderation points, and participate in moderating comments.
				
			    </p>
